cker</a>=C2=A0online, had also been working on censorship circumvention cod=
e. During his detention he was told by the police that he had committed =E2=
=80=9Ccrimes of developing software to help Chinese Internet users scale th=
e Great Fire Wall of China.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0.5em 0px 1.3em;=
padding:0px;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-size:inherit;font-style:inh=
erit;font-variant:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;line-height:21px">Even if it=
&#39;s unclear what law Xu Dong had broken, if any, in November, the legal =
and political climate has grown even more aggressively anti-Internet since =
then. A new=C2=A0<a href=3D"http://chinalawtranslate.com/2015nsl/?lang=3Den=
" style=3D"margin:0px;padding:0px;border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-size:=
